                  To forme and set in order this battaile with facillitie, which in my opinion is the best founded, firme, profitable, and most expedient, and if necessitie did require, more apt to iourney then many other forme of battailes bée: I therfore say it is conuenient for the Sergeant to haue a long practise in Millitarie profession, or else very good Theoricke, or that which is better, both the one and the other together, for if a man do but only possess
